-- Molycorp Shares Drop 11% to Record Low in New York Trading
-- B y   S o n j a   E l m q u i s t
-- 2012-11-12T15:06:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-12/molycorp-shares-drop-11-to-record-low-in-new-york-trading.html
Molycorp Inc. (MCP) , the rare-earth
producer that said last week it’s being investigated by U.S.
Securities and Exchange Commission, dropped to a record low.  Molycorp fell 11 percent to $6.67 at 9:57 a.m. in New York
trading.  The  Greenwood Village , Colorado-based company said in a
Nov. 9 filing that it’s being probed by the SEC over the
accuracy of its public disclosures. The SEC requested
information from Molycorp in August, the company said in
statement later that day.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sonja Elmquist in New York at 
 selmquist1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
